def ResNet18(count_classes):
    model = models.resnet18(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, count_classes)
    return model

def ResNet18_last_layer(count_classes):

    model = models.resnet18(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, 512),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Dropout(0.5),
        nn.Linear(512, count_classes)
    )
    return model

def GoogLeNet(count_classes):
    model = models.googlenet(weights='IMAGENET1K_V1')
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, count_classes)
    return model

def GoogLeNet_last_layer(count_classes):
    model = models.googlenet(weights='IMAGENET1K_V1')

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, 512),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Dropout(0.5),
        nn.Linear(512, count_classes)
    )

    return model

def efficientnet_b0(count_classes):

    model = models.efficientnet_b0(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")
    model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(model.classifier[1].in_features, count_classes)
    return model

def efficientnet_b0_last_layer(count_classes):
    model = models.efficientnet_b0(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    model.classifier = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Dropout(p=0.5),
        nn.Linear(model.classifier[1].in_features, 512),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.BatchNorm1d(512),
        nn.Dropout(p=0.5),
        nn.Linear(512, count_classes),
    )
    return model


def shufflenet(count_classes):

    model = models.shufflenet_v2_x1_0(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, count_classes)

    return model

def shufflenet_last_layer(count_classes):
    model = models.shufflenet_v2_x1_0(weights="IMAGENET1K_V1")

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(
        nn.BatchNorm1d(model.fc.in_features),
        nn.Dropout(0.5),
        nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, 256),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.BatchNorm1d(256),
        nn.Linear(256, count_classes)
    )
    return model

def plot_images(images, labels, classes, rows=2, cols=2):

    np_images = np.clip((images / 2.0 + 0.5).numpy(), 0, 1)
    num_images = min(len(images), rows * cols)

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(rows, cols, figsize=(cols * 2, rows * 2))
    axes = axes.flatten()

    for i in range(num_images):
        axes[i].imshow(np.transpose(np_images[i], (1, 2, 0)))
        axes[i].axis('off')
        axes[i].set_title(classes[labels[i]], fontsize=10)

    for ax in axes[num_images:]:
        ax.axis('off')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In [11]:
def model_device(model):
    return next(model.parameters()).device;

def get_f1(model, data_loader):

    device = model_device(model);
    f1_all = [];

    model.eval();

    for input, labels in data_loader:

        input, labels = input.to(device), labels.to(device)

        outputs = model(input)
        _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)

        f1 = f1_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu(), average="macro")
        f1_all.append(f1)

    return sum(f1_all) / len(f1_all)
In [12]:
def train_model(model, train_data_loader, val_data_loader,
                count_epoch,
                name):

    device = model_device(model);
    optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr = learn_rate);
    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss();

    best_f1 = 0.0;
    macro_f1_score_valid_vector = [];
    loss_vector = [];
    accuracy_vector = [];

    for epoch in range(count_epoch):

        print(f'Epoch {epoch}/{count_epoch - 1}');

        running_corrects = 0;
        running_loss = 0.0;
        total_number_train = 0;


        model.train();
        start_t_train = time.time();
        for input, labels in train_data_loader:

            input, labels = input.to(device), labels.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad();
            outputs = model(input);
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels);
            loss.backward();
            optimizer.step();


            _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)
            running_loss += loss.item() * input.size(0);
            running_corrects += torch.sum(preds == labels.data);
            total_number_train += labels.size(0);
        end_t_train = time.time();

        t_train = end_t_train - start_t_train;

        accuracy_epoch = running_corrects / total_number_train;
        loss_epoch = running_loss / total_number_train;

        start_t_val = time.time();
        macro_f1_score_valid = get_f1(model, val_data_loader);
        end_t_val = time.time();
        t_val = end_t_val - start_t_val;

        if macro_f1_score_valid > best_f1:
            torch.save(model.state_dict(), f"best_{name}.pth")
            best_f1 = macro_f1_score_valid

        macro_f1_score_valid_vector.append(macro_f1_score_valid);
        loss_vector.append(loss_epoch);
        accuracy_vector.append(accuracy_epoch);

        print(f"Train: loss: {loss_epoch:.5f}; accuracy {accuracy_epoch:.5f}; time(sec.) {t_train:.3f}");
        print(f"Validation: macro F1_score: {macro_f1_score_valid:.4f}; time(sec.) {t_val:.3f}");
        print("")

    return macro_f1_score_valid_vector, loss_vector, accuracy_vector

def learn_mod(model, count_epoch):

    name = model.__name__;
    count_classes = len(class_names);
    model = model(count_classes).to(device);

    macro_f1_score_valid_vector, loss_vector, accuracy_vector = train_model(model, train_data_loader, val_data_loader,
                count_epoch,
                name)

    model.load_state_dict(torch.load(f"best_{name}.pth", weights_only=True));

    macro_f1_score_test = get_f1(model, test_data_loader);
    print("/"*20);
    print(f"Test: macro F1_score: {macro_f1_score_test}");

    plt.plot(range(count_epoch), macro_f1_score_valid_vector, marker="o", color = "black")
    #plt.title(f"{name} validation")
    plt.xlabel("epochs")
    plt.xticks([i for i in range(count_epoch)])
    plt.ylabel("F1 score")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

    f1_vector_different_model[name] = macro_f1_score_test;
